The paper presents a procedure for splitting processes in a process algebra with multi-actions, which is a topic related to formal methods and logic (cs.LO). The procedure is applied to the coordination language Reo, which is a topic related to programming languages and software engineering (cs.PL, cs.SE). The paper also discusses the performance improvement of connectors, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and formal languages (cs.FL).
